{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0172ydGJhLMpgGwPGbDcVziE","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# mongodb/statefulset-customization\n2\t# Restore a stable 3-member MongoDB replica set after StatefulSet customization breaks readiness\n3\t\n4\tparams:\n5\t  cluster_prefix:\n6\t    default: mongodb-replica\n7\t    description: App label / StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n8\t  replica_set_name:\n9\t    default: mongodb-replica\n10\t    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n11\t  admin_username:\n12\t    default: admin-user\n13\t    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n14\t  template_label_key:\n15\t    default: monitoring\n16\t    description: Pod template label key toggled by the customization.\n17\t  template_label_value:\n18\t    default: enabled\n19\t    description: Solved value the agent must restore for the template label.\n20\t  faulty_request_memory:\n21\t    default: 128Mi\n22\t    description: Faulty memory request applied to break readiness.\n23\t  faulty_limit_memory:\n24\t    default: 256Mi\n25\t    description: Faulty memory limit applied to break readiness.\n26\t\n27\tprompt: |\n28\t  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace with auth enabled.\n29\t  Pods never become Ready, and monitoring cannot see them.\n30\t\n31\t  Task:\n32\t  - Restore a stable 3-member replica set without data loss.\n33\t  - All pods must become Ready.\n34\t  - Replica set should have 1 PRIMARY and 2 SECONDARY members.\n35\t  - Restore the pod-template `{{params.template_label_key}}` label to\n36\t    `{{params.template_label_value}}` so monitoring can see the members.\n37\t\n38\t  Notes:\n39\t  - No operators or CRDs.\n40\t\n41\tnamespace_contract:\n42\t  required_roles: []\n43\t\n44\tmetrics:\n45\t  - time_to_first_mutation\n46\t\n47\tpreconditionUnits:\n48\t  - name: mongo_env_ready\n49\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n50\t    probe:\n51\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pod {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n52\t        timeout_sec: 10\n53\t    apply:\n54\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true'\"\n55\t        sleep: 2\n56\t      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n57\t        sleep: 1\n58\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n59\t        sleep: 1\n60\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/guard-script.yaml\"\n61\t        sleep: 1\n62\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/services.yaml\"\n63\t        sleep: 1\n64\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n65\t        sleep: 5\n66\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb wait --for=condition=ready pod -l app={{params.cluster_prefix}} --timeout=300s\"\n67\t        sleep: 2\n68\t      # Pod-Ready != mongod accepting TCP (§1.10). Poll ping-until-ok before the\n69\t      # first mongosh call so rs.initiate doesn't hit MongoNetworkError ECONNREFUSED.\n70\t      - command: |\n71\t          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 30); do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok'\\'' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1 && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\n72\t        sleep: 2\n73\t      - command: |\n74\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[{_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}]})'\\'''\n75\t        sleep: 5\n76\t      - command: |\n77\t          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 20); do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.hello().isWritablePrimary'\\'' | grep true && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\n78\t        sleep: 2\n79\t      - command: |\n80\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.admin_username}}\",pwd:\"admin123password\",roles:[{role:\"clusterAdmin\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"userAdminAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"readWriteAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"}]})'\\'''\n81\t        sleep: 2\n82\t      - command: |\n83\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb patch sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} --type=json -p='\\''[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/metadata/labels/{{params.template_label_key}}\",\"value\":\"disabled\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/requests/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/limits/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_limit_memory}}\"}]'\\'''\n84\t        sleep: 2\n85\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb delete pod -l app={{params.cluster_prefix}}\"\n86\t        sleep: 2\n87\t    verify:\n88\t      # The precondition deliberately breaks the statefulset (faulty memory\n89\t      # patch + pod restart) for the agent to fix, so pods are NOT expected to\n90\t      # be Running here -- verify the broken baseline statefulset is in place.\n91\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o name\"\n92\t        timeout_sec: 10\n93\t\n94\t  - name: admin_user_fixture\n95\t    # Composition self-sufficiency: this case authenticates as the `admin-user`\n96\t    # created at deploy. On an inherited cluster a no-auth/other predecessor may\n97\t    # not have created it, and a live user's password is unrecoverable -> the\n98\t    # oracle's (and the user fixtures') admin auth fails through no agent fault.\n99\t    # Bring our own additively: if admin-user already authenticates, skip; else\n100\t    # ensure the secret and create the user. No restart, no data touched,\n101\t    # idempotent -> never regresses a cluster where admin already works.\n102\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n103\t    probe:\n104\t      - command: |\n105\t          /bin/sh -c '\n106\t          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n107\t          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null)\n108\t          [ -n \"$pw\" ] || exit 1\n109\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval \"db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1\n110\t          '\n111\t        timeout_sec: 30\n112\t    apply:\n113\t      # Ensure the admin secret (idempotent: create only if missing).\n114\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb create secret generic admin-user-password --from-literal=password=admin123password'\"\n115\t        sleep: 1\n116\t      # Ensure the admin-user MongoDB user. On a no-auth inherited cluster this\n117\t      # runs unauthenticated and succeeds; where it already exists it errors and\n118\t      # the `|| true` keeps it a no-op. Never drops or alters existing users/data.\n119\t      - command: |\n120\t          /bin/sh -c '\n121\t          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n122\t          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t --eval \"db.getSiblingDB(\\\"admin\\\").createUser({user:\\\"{{params.admin_username}}\\\",pwd:\\\"admin123password\\\",roles:[{role:\\\"root\\\",db:\\\"admin\\\"}]})\" 2>/dev/null || true\n123\t          '\n124\t        sleep: 2\n125\t    verify:\n126\t      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo ok'\"\n127\t        timeout_sec: 15\n128\t\n129\t  # Problem-shape replant (composition safety, Pattern 1): the planted fault is a\n130\t  # StatefulSet template carrying label {{params.template_label_key}}=disabled AND\n131\t  # too-low memory requests/limits ({{params.faulty_request_memory}} /\n132\t  # {{params.faulty_limit_memory}}) that break readiness. The oracle grades that\n133\t  # the agent set the label to {{params.template_label_value}} (default `enabled`)\n134\t  # and raised memory above the minimums. Both are planted only inside the\n135\t  # destructive mongo_env_ready.apply, which is SKIPPED on an inherited cluster ->\n136\t  # the template label never exists (`got None`) and the memory is already fine, so\n137\t  # the agent has nothing to fix yet the oracle still fails. This unit re-plants the\n138\t  # EXACT drift (label=disabled + faulty memory) onto the LIVE StatefulSet via a\n139\t  # targeted patch, then rolls the pods so they go non-Ready. It patches ONLY the\n140\t  # template label and the mongod container memory -- never the image/version or\n141\t  # other config -- so it is safe over a carried-over cluster. Standalone the\n142\t  # probe sees the drift already present and skips -> identical behaviour.\n143\t  - name: statefulset_customization_drift_ready\n144\t    on_probe_fail: skip\n145\t    probe:\n146\t      # True (skip) when the unsolved drift is ALREADY present: template label is\n147\t      # NOT the solved value OR memory request is below the oracle minimum. False\n148\t      # (apply) when the StatefulSet is in the solved/healthy state and the drift\n149\t      # must be re-planted.\n150\t      - command: |\n151\t          /bin/sh -c '\n152\t          lbl=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.metadata.labels.{{params.template_label_key}}}\" 2>/dev/null)\n153\t          mem=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.requests.memory}\" 2>/dev/null)\n154\t          [ \"$lbl\" != \"{{params.template_label_value}}\" ] || [ \"$mem\" = \"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\" ]\n155\t          '\n156\t        timeout_sec: 15\n157\t    apply:\n158\t      - command: |\n159\t          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb patch sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} --type=json -p='\\''[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/metadata/labels/{{params.template_label_key}}\",\"value\":\"disabled\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/requests/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/limits/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_limit_memory}}\"}]'\\'' 2>/dev/null || kubectl -n mongodb patch sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} --type=merge -p '\\''{\"spec\":{\"template\":{\"metadata\":{\"labels\":{\"{{params.template_label_key}}\":\"disabled\"}},\"spec\":{\"containers\":[{\"name\":\"mongod\",\"resources\":{\"requests\":{\"memory\":\"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\"},\"limits\":{\"memory\":\"{{params.faulty_limit_memory}}\"}}}]}}}}'\\'''\n160\t        sleep: 2\n161\t      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb delete pod -l app={{params.cluster_prefix}}\"\n162\t        sleep: 2\n163\t    verify:\n164\t      - command: |\n165\t          /bin/sh -c 'lbl=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.metadata.labels.{{params.template_label_key}}}\" 2>/dev/null); [ \"$lbl\" = \"disabled\" ]'\n166\t        timeout_sec: 15\n167\t\n168\toracle:\n169\t  verify:\n170\t    commands:\n171\t      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/oracle/oracle.py\"\n172\t        timeout_sec: 60\n173\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51099fc9-f5ed-4260-80ad-92cedb39ef33","uuid":"303915ea-60d4-4cc1-8aed-8a0c9d535f79","timestamp":"2026-06-24T05:41:31.990Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mydata/karma/cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/test.yaml","content":"# mongodb/statefulset-customization\n# Restore a stable 3-member MongoDB replica set after StatefulSet customization breaks readiness\n\nparams:\n  cluster_prefix:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: App label / StatefulSet name of the replica set members.\n  replica_set_name:\n    default: mongodb-replica\n    description: MongoDB replica set _id used when initiating the set.\n  admin_username:\n    default: admin-user\n    description: Username of the MongoDB admin user.\n  template_label_key:\n    default: monitoring\n    description: Pod template label key toggled by the customization.\n  template_label_value:\n    default: enabled\n    description: Solved value the agent must restore for the template label.\n  faulty_request_memory:\n    default: 128Mi\n    description: Faulty memory request applied to break readiness.\n  faulty_limit_memory:\n    default: 256Mi\n    description: Faulty memory limit applied to break readiness.\n\nprompt: |\n  A 3-member MongoDB replica set is running in the mongodb namespace with auth enabled.\n  Pods never become Ready, and monitoring cannot see them.\n\n  Task:\n  - Restore a stable 3-member replica set without data loss.\n  - All pods must become Ready.\n  - Replica set should have 1 PRIMARY and 2 SECONDARY members.\n  - Restore the pod-template `{{params.template_label_key}}` label to\n    `{{params.template_label_value}}` so monitoring can see the members.\n\n  Notes:\n  - No operators or CRDs.\n\nnamespace_contract:\n  required_roles: []\n\nmetrics:\n  - time_to_first_mutation\n\npreconditionUnits:\n  - name: mongo_env_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get pod {{params.cluster_prefix}}-0 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n    apply:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl delete namespace mongodb --ignore-not-found=true; kubectl wait --for=delete namespace/mongodb --timeout=120s || true'\"\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl create namespace mongodb\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/secrets.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/guard-script.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/services.yaml\"\n        sleep: 1\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb apply -f cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/resource/statefulset.yaml\"\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb wait --for=condition=ready pod -l app={{params.cluster_prefix}} --timeout=300s\"\n        sleep: 2\n      # Pod-Ready != mongod accepting TCP (§1.10). Poll ping-until-ok before the\n      # first mongosh call so rs.initiate doesn't hit MongoNetworkError ECONNREFUSED.\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 30); do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok'\\'' 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1 && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''rs.initiate({_id:\"{{params.replica_set_name}}\",members:[{_id:0,host:\"mongodb-replica-0.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:1,host:\"mongodb-replica-1.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"},{_id:2,host:\"mongodb-replica-2.mongodb-replica-svc.mongodb.svc.cluster.local:27017\"}]})'\\'''\n        sleep: 5\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'for i in $(seq 1 20); do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.hello().isWritablePrimary'\\'' | grep true && exit 0; sleep 3; done; exit 1'\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet --eval '\\''db.getSiblingDB(\"admin\").createUser({user:\"{{params.admin_username}}\",pwd:\"admin123password\",roles:[{role:\"clusterAdmin\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"userAdminAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"},{role:\"readWriteAnyDatabase\",db:\"admin\"}]})'\\'''\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb patch sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} --type=json -p='\\''[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/metadata/labels/{{params.template_label_key}}\",\"value\":\"disabled\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/requests/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/limits/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_limit_memory}}\"}]'\\'''\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb delete pod -l app={{params.cluster_prefix}}\"\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      # The precondition deliberately breaks the statefulset (faulty memory\n      # patch + pod restart) for the agent to fix, so pods are NOT expected to\n      # be Running here -- verify the broken baseline statefulset is in place.\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb get statefulset {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o name\"\n        timeout_sec: 10\n\n  - name: admin_user_fixture\n    # Composition self-sufficiency: this case authenticates as the `admin-user`\n    # created at deploy. On an inherited cluster a no-auth/other predecessor may\n    # not have created it, and a live user's password is unrecoverable -> the\n    # oracle's (and the user fixtures') admin auth fails through no agent fault.\n    # Bring our own additively: if admin-user already authenticates, skip; else\n    # ensure the secret and create the user. No restart, no data touched,\n    # idempotent -> never regresses a cluster where admin already works.\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          pw=$(kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password -o jsonpath=\"{.data.password}\" 2>/dev/null | base64 -d 2>/dev/null)\n          [ -n \"$pw\" ] || exit 1\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t \"mongodb://{{params.admin_username}}:$pw@localhost:27017/admin\" --eval \"db.runCommand({ping:1}).ok\" 2>/dev/null | grep -q 1\n          '\n        timeout_sec: 30\n    apply:\n      # Ensure the admin secret (idempotent: create only if missing).\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 || kubectl -n mongodb create secret generic admin-user-password --from-literal=password=admin123password'\"\n        sleep: 1\n      # Ensure the admin-user MongoDB user. On a no-auth inherited cluster this\n      # runs unauthenticated and succeeds; where it already exists it errors and\n      # the `|| true` keeps it a no-op. Never drops or alters existing users/data.\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          t=\"\"; for cca in /etc/tls/ca.crt /etc/mongo-ca/ca.crt; do kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- ls $cca >/dev/null 2>&1 && { t=\"--tls --tlsAllowInvalidHostnames --tlsAllowInvalidCertificates --tlsCAFile $cca\"; break; }; done\n          kubectl -n mongodb exec mongodb-replica-0 -- mongosh --quiet $t --eval \"db.getSiblingDB(\\\"admin\\\").createUser({user:\\\"{{params.admin_username}}\\\",pwd:\\\"admin123password\\\",roles:[{role:\\\"root\\\",db:\\\"admin\\\"}]})\" 2>/dev/null || true\n          '\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: \"/bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb get secret admin-user-password >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo ok'\"\n        timeout_sec: 15\n\n  # Problem-shape replant (composition safety, Pattern 1): the planted fault is a\n  # StatefulSet template carrying label {{params.template_label_key}}=disabled AND\n  # too-low memory requests/limits ({{params.faulty_request_memory}} /\n  # {{params.faulty_limit_memory}}) that break readiness. The oracle grades that\n  # the agent set the label to {{params.template_label_value}} (default `enabled`)\n  # and raised memory above the minimums. Both are planted only inside the\n  # destructive mongo_env_ready.apply, which is SKIPPED on an inherited cluster ->\n  # the template label never exists (`got None`) and the memory is already fine, so\n  # the agent has nothing to fix yet the oracle still fails. This unit re-plants the\n  # EXACT drift (label=disabled + faulty memory) onto the LIVE StatefulSet via a\n  # targeted patch, then rolls the pods so they go non-Ready. It patches ONLY the\n  # template label and the mongod container memory -- never the image/version or\n  # other config -- so it is safe over a carried-over cluster. Standalone the\n  # probe sees the drift already present and skips -> identical behaviour.\n  - name: statefulset_customization_drift_ready\n    on_probe_fail: skip\n    probe:\n      # True (skip) when the unsolved drift is ALREADY present: template label is\n      # NOT the solved value OR memory request is below the oracle minimum. False\n      # (apply) when the StatefulSet is in the solved/healthy state and the drift\n      # must be re-planted.\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c '\n          lbl=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.metadata.labels.{{params.template_label_key}}}\" 2>/dev/null)\n          mem=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.spec.containers[0].resources.requests.memory}\" 2>/dev/null)\n          [ \"$lbl\" != \"{{params.template_label_value}}\" ] || [ \"$mem\" = \"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\" ]\n          '\n        timeout_sec: 15\n    apply:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'kubectl -n mongodb patch sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} --type=json -p='\\''[{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/metadata/labels/{{params.template_label_key}}\",\"value\":\"disabled\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/requests/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\"},{\"op\":\"replace\",\"path\":\"/spec/template/spec/containers/0/resources/limits/memory\",\"value\":\"{{params.faulty_limit_memory}}\"}]'\\'' 2>/dev/null || kubectl -n mongodb patch sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} --type=merge -p '\\''{\"spec\":{\"template\":{\"metadata\":{\"labels\":{\"{{params.template_label_key}}\":\"disabled\"}},\"spec\":{\"containers\":[{\"name\":\"mongod\",\"resources\":{\"requests\":{\"memory\":\"{{params.faulty_request_memory}}\"},\"limits\":{\"memory\":\"{{params.faulty_limit_memory}}\"}}}]}}}}'\\'''\n        sleep: 2\n      - command: \"kubectl -n mongodb delete pod -l app={{params.cluster_prefix}}\"\n        sleep: 2\n    verify:\n      - command: |\n          /bin/sh -c 'lbl=$(kubectl -n mongodb get sts {{params.cluster_prefix}} -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.template.metadata.labels.{{params.template_label_key}}}\" 2>/dev/null); [ \"$lbl\" = \"disabled\" ]'\n        timeout_sec: 15\n\noracle:\n  verify:\n    commands:\n      - command: \"python3 cases/mongodb/statefulset-customization/oracle/oracle.py\"\n        timeout_sec: 60\n","numLines":173,"startLine":1,"totalLines":173}}}
