{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VRZpKsSTqTPr4U8zz6LUuY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks are complete. Here's what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The StatefulSet had three broken settings that caused the `pod-guard` init container to fail:\n1. `monitoring` label was `disabled` (guard requires `enabled`)\n2. `requests.memory` was `128Mi` (guard requires ≥ 512Mi)\n3. `limits.memory` was `256Mi` (guard requires ≥ 1024Mi)\n\n**Fix:** A single `kubectl patch` corrected all three fields at once, allowing pods to pass the guard check and start.\n\n**Current state:**\n- All 3 pods: `1/1 Running`\n- Replica set: `mongodb-replica-1` PRIMARY, `mongodb-replica-0` and `mongodb-replica-2` SECONDARY\n- Template label: `monitoring=enabled`\n- Memory: `requests=512Mi`, `limits=1Gi`\n- Data preserved in PVCs (no data loss — pods were restarted, not deleted with PVCs)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":282,"cache_read_input_tokens":63057,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":282},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"51099fc9-f5ed-4260-80ad-92cedb39ef33","uuid":"d539a5f7-11b7-41d0-a12b-f75ff7810c29","request_id":"req_011CcMYsKjR4EbcmNfcnp7Tp"}
